      "writtenOn": "2016-11-28T18:25:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I thought about this too and in my understanding of how boltdb works, it should not make a different. \nAt least within an transaction it will cache all pages that it loads. Even if I did a direct bucket.Get(...) it will do a \nCursor seek first. \nSee https://github.com/boltdb/bolt/blob/master/bucket.go#L268",
      "parentUuid": "4df48341_8d19e0a4",
      "revId": "c9809743d5fb55cba6369600438261c48fdf39e5",
